author: Inside Edition
description: Jaden King and her boyfriend Michael Bevers were excited to get their new mattress, and they were in for quite a surprise when the mattress suddenly popped out. Inside Edition learned there is actually a correct way of unwrapping your new mattress.
title: How To Open A Vacuum-Sealed Mattress Correctly #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Folks can't stop talking about Sydney Sweeney's eye-popping sheer dress that left little to the imagination. Megyn Kelly lashed out at the actress, giving the look a thumbs down.
title: Sydney Sweeney's Gets Scolded For Sheer Dress #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A newborn in Minnesota has been a fighter since before she entered the world. Little Hazel has hydrocephalus, a condition that doesn’t allow her brain to drain fluid properly. When the baby was born, her parents found out she has the rare condition known as Moebius Syndrome which doesn’t allow her to blink or show facial expressions. The family has set up a GoFundMe to help pay for expenses- https://www.gofundme.com/f/help-tori-and-her-five-special-needs-children-find-a-home
title: Baby Born with Rare Syndrome That Doesn’t Allow Her To Close Her Eyes

author: Inside Edition
description: Anguished 911 calls from a deadly incident in September were released. Maria Niotis and Isabella Salas, both 17 years old, were struck by an SUV driven by Vincent Battiloro on a street in Cranford, New Jersey. Both Niotis and Salas died in the incident. Battiloro, who is being tried as a juvenile, was allegedly stalking one of the girls. Attorney Brent Bramnick spoke to Inside Edition's Steven Fabian about the incident.
title: 911 Calls Released In New Jersey Car Attack That Killed Two Teens
